    <member name="T:System.SystemException">
      <dduexml xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5">
        <summary>
          <para>Defines the base class for predefined exceptions in the <codeEntityReference autoUpgrade="true">N:System</codeEntityReference> namespace.</para>
        </summary>
        <remarks>
          <content>
            <para>This class is provided as a means to differentiate between exceptions defined by the system versus exceptions defined by applications.</para>
            <para>
              <codeEntityReference autoUpgrade="true">T:System.SystemException</codeEntityReference> does not provide information as to the cause of the <codeEntityReference autoUpgrade="true">T:System.Exception</codeEntityReference>. In most scenarios, instances of this class should not be thrown. In cases where this class is instantiated, a human-readable message describing the error should be passed to the constructor.</para>
            <para>
              <codeEntityReference autoUpgrade="true">T:System.SystemException</codeEntityReference> is thrown by the common language runtime when errors occur that are nonfatal and recoverable by user programs. These errors result from failed runtime check (such as an array out-of-bound error), and can occur during the execution of any method. <codeEntityReference autoUpgrade="true">T:System.SystemException</codeEntityReference> adds no new functionality to <codeEntityReference autoUpgrade="true">T:System.Exception</codeEntityReference>.</para>
            <para>
              <codeEntityReference autoUpgrade="true">T:System.SystemException</codeEntityReference> uses the HRESULT COR_E_SYSTEM, that has the value 0x80131501.</para>
            <para>For a list of initial property values for an instance of <codeEntityReference autoUpgrade="true">T:System.SystemException</codeEntityReference>, see the <codeEntityReference autoUpgrade="true">M:System.SystemException.#ctor</codeEntityReference> constructors.</para>
            <para>For more information on exceptions defined by applications, see <codeEntityReference autoUpgrade="true">T:System.ApplicationException</codeEntityReference>.</para>
          </content>
        </remarks>
        <relatedTopics>
          <codeEntityReference autoUpgrade="true">T:System.Exception</codeEntityReference>
